{"word":"πλήθω","slug":"πλήθω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πλήθω</b></el> <el>(πλήθω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:poetically'>poet.</a> <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>πέπληθα</el>, in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> sense\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> form of <a href='S:πίμπλημι'><el>πίμπλημι</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>mostly in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πίμπλημι'><el>πίμπλημι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be</i> or <i>become full of</i> a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <el>χεῖρας κρεῶν πλήθοντες</el> <i>having</i> them <i>full of</i> flesh, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:dative'>dat.</a>, <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b>: <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> of rivers, <i>to be full, brimming</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; so, <el>πλήθουσα Σελήνη</el> <i>at her full</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>ἀγορᾶς πληθούσης, ἐν ἀγορᾷ πληθούσῃ</el>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>, <a href='S:vide'>v.</a> sub <el>ἀγορά</el> <a href='S:vide'>V.</a><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:transitive'>trans.</a>, like <el>πληθύνω</el>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}